      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): retry restart continuation recovery",
        "body": "## What changed\n\n- Added periodic restart/session-delivery recovery so entries deferred by retry backoff are retried after startup.\n- Added a focused gateway lifecycle regression test that proves the first startup recovery and later 60s retry both call restart-continuation recovery.\n\nFixes #76087\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Restart/session delivery recovery now runs the startup drain and then continues retrying deferred restart-continuation deliveries while the gateway process is alive. Before this PR, `recoverPendingSessionDeliveries()` scheduled one startup recovery after `1_250ms`; after this PR, it also schedules a `60_000ms` periodic retry.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on Darwin 25.5.0 arm64, Node v26.0.0, pnpm 11.2.2, branch `fastino-76087-restart-continuation-retry`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. Ran a local source-checkout behavior probe against `activateGatewayScheduledServices` and recorded the recovery timers it creates.\n  2. Ran `pnpm test src/gateway/server-runtime-services.test.ts src/infra/session-delivery-queue.recovery.test.ts src/gateway/server-restart-sentinel.test.ts`.\n  3. Ran `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD`.\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal transcript from the local source-checkout behavior probe:\n\n  ```text\n  $ pnpm exec tsx --eval '(async () => { const timers = []; const handle = { unref() {} }; globalThis.setTimeout = (_fn, delay) => { timers.push({ kind: \"timeout\", delay: Number(delay) }); return handle; }; globalThis.setInterval = (_fn, delay) => { timers.push({ kind: \"interval\", delay: Number(delay) }); return handle; }; const { activateGatewayScheduledServices } = await import(\"./src/gateway/server-runtime-services.ts\"); activateGatewayScheduledServices({ minimalTestGateway: false, cfgAtStart: { models: { pricing: { enabled: false } } }, deps: {}, sessionDeliveryRecoveryMaxEnqueuedAt: 123, cron: { start: async () => undefined }, logCron: { error: console.error }, log: { child: (name) => ({ error: (message) => console.log(name + \":\" + message) }), error: (message) => console.log(message), warn: (message) => console.log(message), info: () => undefined, debug: () => undefined } }); console.log(JSON.stringify(timers.filter((timer) => timer.delay === 1250 || timer.delay === 60000))); })();'\n  [heartbeat] started\n  [{\"kind\":\"timeout\",\"delay\":1250},{\"kind\":\"interval\",\"delay\":60000}]\n  ```\n\n  Supplemental focused test output:\n\n  ```text\n  Test Files  4 passed (4)\n  Tests  74 passed (74)\n\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  6 passed (6)\n\n  [test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 12.49s\n  ```\n- Observed result after fix: The gateway scheduled-services path creates both the startup `1250` ms recovery timeout and the new `60000` ms periodic retry interval for restart-continuation delivery recovery.\n- What was not tested: No live Telegram network outage or production gateway credential flow. No permanent Telegram API failure path; this PR covers the gateway scheduler retry path for pending restart-continuation deliveries.\n",
        "branch": "fastino-76087-restart-continuation-retry",
